# InSync Systems — Company Overview

## Company Profile

InSync Systems Inc. is a privately owned, boutique Canadian IT resourcing and consulting services company headquartered in Calgary, Alberta. Founded over 20 years ago, the firm has grown into one of the largest Canadian-owned IT staffing and solutions companies in Western Canada. InSync is certified as over 50% women-owned and operated.

The company operates from three offices across Western Canada: Calgary, Edmonton, and Vancouver.

**Website:** [insyncsystems.ca](https://insyncsystems.ca/)
**LinkedIn:** [InSync Systems on LinkedIn](https://ca.linkedin.com/company/insync-systems)

## Leadership

**CorryAnn Struik** — Owner. CorryAnn guides InSync's strategic planning, delivery offerings, and partnerships. She is known for building world-class client service teams that transform how companies design offerings and bring them to market. CorryAnn was the initial contact for the Stealth EA engagement discussion (met April 29, 2026).

**Bruce McRitchie** — Vice President, Client Solution Services. Bruce provides strategic guidance to the organisation and its clients, bringing 40 years of business, consulting, and customer service experience. His background includes roles at SAP, Fujitsu, Burntsand, Illumiti, and SHL Systemhouse. He has extensive knowledge of the Calgary IT market.

## Services

InSync provides expert contract personnel, formal augmentation outsourcing, and managed service arrangements to strengthen IT departments and business units. Their core service lines include:

**IT Resourcing & Staffing** — Staff augmentation, contract-to-perm, and permanent placement. InSync maintains Practice Leads who are senior subject-matter experts responsible for vetting candidates and ensuring technical excellence and cultural alignment.

**IT Managed Services** — Managed service arrangements for ongoing IT operational needs.

**IT Co-Source Provisioning** — Hybrid models blending client and InSync resources.

**Solution Delivery** — Professional services and project-based delivery.

**Program & Project Management** — Oversight and delivery management for client initiatives.

## Practice Areas & Certifications

InSync differentiates through credentialed Practice Leads across several disciplines:

- **Enterprise Architecture** — TOGAF-trained architects establishing technology blueprints and future-proofing organisations
- **Security** — CISSP consultants embedding security by design
- **Data & Analytics** — Certified data professionals transforming datasets into governed, self-service dashboards and predictive models
- **Quality Assurance** — ISTQB-certified QA teams combining automated and exploratory testing
- **Change Management** — Prosci-certified change practitioners designing communication, training, and sponsorship plans
- **Infrastructure** — CCIE- and AWS-certified engineers designing, implementing, and supporting resilient on-prem, hybrid, and cloud infrastructures with 24×7 monitoring

## Industries Served

InSync has worked with hundreds of companies across Western Canada and beyond, with particular depth in:

- **Oil and Gas** — Supporting organisations with skilled talent and custom digital solutions that enhance operations, safety, and field efficiency
- **Banking and Fintech** — Expert consultants and delivery teams for secure, high-performance systems
- **Public Sector / Government** — Delivering secure, accessible digital services
- **Education** — Modernising critical student information systems and developing learning platforms
- **Telecom**
- **Utilities**

